				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Could you clarify your &quot;no&quot;? My understanding is that a proper interlaced signal basically has a flag every other frame (never mind how it's encoded) that causes the display to offset the field half a scanline vertically, and that these these offset and non-offset fields are referred to as even and odd (again, irrelevant which is which for this post). The NES doesn't set this flag every other field, and thus the TV always displays the same field every frame. Hence my comment, it shows the same field (even/odd, not relevant here which) every frame. The same field implies that its scanlines are always on the same physical position on the CRT face, since that's what the even/odd means.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

