				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Scanlines at the same position each field is the definition of progressive. There are 240 of those lines, making the signal 240p. Yes, a given CRT will have more prominent space between the scanlines when displaying a 240p signal than when displaying a 480i signal. No, that doesn't make the signal any less 240p, just as a 350-line picture from a VGA card in full-screen EGA-compatible mode doesn't suddenly become 700p with every other line blank when displayed on a VGA monitor tuned for 768p.</div>

